# px4_realtime_plot.py — trigger modes, active-only plots, attitude plots

## Context

`px4_realtime_plot.py` is a single-file real-time MAVLink plotter. Today it only
refreshes/saves while the vehicle is **armed** (using arm state as a proxy for
"SD logger recording"), plots only **Position NED** and **Velocity NED**, has no
attitude plots, and reads message fields directly (`msg.x`) with no existence
guards. It connects via `udpin:127.0.0.1:14551`, which correctly matches the
`[UdpEndpoint plotter]` (127.0.0.1:14551, Mode=Normal) in
`~/.config/mavlink-router/main.conf` — so the default is right.

The user wants it to be useful beyond arm-gated capture (to mirror PX4's
`SDLOG_MODE` "log from start" behavior), to avoid showing empty plots for sensors
that aren't producing data, to add attitude / attitude-rate plots with setpoint
overlays, and to be robust to missing message fields.

**Confirmed decisions:** `--trigger arm/start/auto`; only-active **on by default**
(`--show-all` to override); attitude in **degrees**.

All changes land in one file: `/home/choudhury/tools/dev/px4_plotter/px4_realtime_plot.py`.

