## Critical correctness note (verified against pymavlink 2.4.49)

`ATTITUDE_TARGET.type_mask` bits:
`BODY_ROLL_RATE_IGNORE=1`, `BODY_PITCH_RATE_IGNORE=2`, `BODY_YAW_RATE_IGNORE=4`,
`THROTTLE_IGNORE=64`, **`ATTITUDE_IGNORE=128`**. The quaternion-ignore bit is
**128, not 64** — PX4 routinely sets the throttle-ignore bit (64), so testing 64
would wrongly blank the attitude setpoint on every message. Encode via the named
enum constants so it can't drift.

